      "title": "Pull Request Control for Revit",
      "category": "speaking",
      "visible": true,
      "highlight": false,
      "includeInResume": false,
      "cover": "/speaking/aec-hackathon-2025/cover.jpg",
      "date": "2025",
      "location": "New York, NY",
      "event": "AEC Hackathon",
      "abstract": "Proposed and prototyped a pull-request-style review workflow for Revit models, bringing version-control concepts from software engineering into BIM collaboration. The system enables architects and engineers to branch, diff, and merge Revit model changes with a structured review process - similar to GitHub pull requests - so teams can catch clashes, track who changed what, and approve modifications before they land in the central model. Built during the 2025 AEC Hackathon, the proof-of-concept leverages the Revit API and a lightweight web dashboard to visualize model deltas and manage review threads across disciplines."
    },
